  "updateinfo_id": "ALSA-2026:20600",
  "description": "The wireshark packages contain a network protocol analyzer used to capture and browse the traffic running on a computer network.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * wireshark: Heap-based Buffer Overflow in Wireshark (CVE-2026-5405)\n  * wireshark: Improper Limitation of a Pathname to a Restricted Directory ('Path Traversal') in Wireshark (CVE-2026-5656)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
